00:27.931 --> 00:28.931
Valerie?

00:34.756 --> 00:35.989
The door was open.

00:38.969 --> 00:39.969
John?

00:41.581 --> 00:42.648
Are you okay?

00:43.190 --> 00:44.190
Oh, my god.

00:56.169 --> 00:58.135
Somebody call the police!

00:58.314 --> 01:00.639
Please!
Please help!

01:05.120 --> 01:08.773
Mr. Monk, 14 years ago you were the
chief investigator of this crime scene.

01:08.847 --> 01:11.480
It was your testimony that put
max barton behind bars.

01:11.566 --> 01:14.678
As you know, mr. Barton's eligible
to be paroled at the end of this month.

01:14.711 --> 01:17.588
I understand you'd like to make
a statement before our final decision.

01:17.621 --> 01:18.974
Yes, sir.
Thank you.

01:19.061 --> 01:22.501
I've been a homicide investigator
for more than 20 years.

01:22.551 --> 01:26.365
I have seen more crime scenes
than I could possibly count.

01:26.431 --> 01:28.265
Well, 410, but...

01:28.407 --> 01:29.740
That's not the point.

01:30.081 --> 01:33.297
What I saw that 
morning in that house

01:34.817 --> 01:37.851
was beyond imagination.
What he did

01:38.115 --> 01:42.399
to those people, the...
The husband had been tortured.

01:42.598 --> 01:45.498
We found the wife in the backyard.
She had...

01:47.942 --> 01:50.775
She had tried
to crawl away...

01:52.511 --> 01:53.828
Take your time, mr. Monk.

01:54.144 --> 01:57.211
I've tried to forget it,
but I can't.

01:57.251 --> 02:00.171
And I'm sure that sarah mcnally,
who found the bodies,

02:00.271 --> 02:01.838
will never forget it either.

02:04.649 --> 02:08.805
Putting people like max barton behind
bars is the reason I became a cop.

02:08.920 --> 02:10.737
In my opinion,

02:11.440 --> 02:15.862
he should never be released. He should
never be considered for release.

02:16.114 --> 02:17.604
- He...
- Ms. Lawrence.

02:17.814 --> 02:19.175
Is there a problem?

02:19.714 --> 02:20.714
Excuse me.

02:21.008 --> 02:23.262
Commissioner, members of the board,

02:23.611 --> 02:26.613
mr. Barton would like to withdraw
his application for parole.

02:26.778 --> 02:28.511
- Withdraw?
- Yes, sir...

02:28.568 --> 02:31.080
This is daniel crosby
of the innocence league.

02:31.180 --> 02:34.180
The federal appeals court
has exonerated mr. Barton.

02:34.497 --> 02:36.230
He will be released
by the end of the week.

02:37.557 --> 02:38.957
Uh, what...

02:39.490 --> 02:40.857
What's going on?

02:40.997 --> 02:42.414
It's a new dna test.

02:42.831 --> 02:43.831
Dna?

02:44.177 --> 02:46.410
They've retested the
crime scene evidence.

02:46.477 --> 02:49.289
Apparently, the blood at the scene
under the victim's fingernails

02:49.323 --> 02:51.062
does not belong to mr. Barton.

02:51.934 --> 02:53.360
May I say something?

02:53.567 --> 02:55.684
I'm afraid it's too late, Ms. Mcnally.

02:55.851 --> 02:56.901
There's been a mistake.

02:58.033 --> 03:00.983
Uh...
A mistake?

03:01.723 --> 03:04.756
Looks like you got
the wrong man, Mr. Monk.

